# DLP exact-match fingerprints -- consumed by scripts/dlp_fingerprint_scan.py
#
# This .example file is INERT. To enable exact-data-match scanning, copy it to
# `fingerprints.txt` (same dir) and add SHA-256 hashes:
#
#     cp .claude/dlp/fingerprints.txt.example .claude/dlp/fingerprints.txt
#
# The scanner hashes each candidate token in a diff and fails the build on a match.
# You store ONLY the hashes here -- the raw sensitive value never enters the repo.
#
# Format: one lowercase SHA-256 hex digest per line. `#` starts a comment.
# Any line that is not exactly 64 hex chars is ignored.
#
# Generate a fingerprint for a known-sensitive token (canary string, a specific
# customer email, an internal hostname):
#
#     printf '%s' 'the-secret-value' | sha256sum        # Linux
#     python -c "import hashlib,sys;print(hashlib.sha256(sys.argv[1].encode()).hexdigest())" 'the-secret-value'
#
# Tokenization note: the scanner splits on non-[A-Za-z0-9._@+/-] and hashes tokens
# of >= 8 chars, so fingerprint whole tokens (e.g. an email or hostname), not
# phrases with spaces.

# --- add your fingerprint hashes below (64 hex chars each) ---
# e3b0c44298fc1c149afbf4c8996fb92427ae41e4649b934ca495991b7852b855   # example: sha256 of ""
